line_1: In the Wilds of Hibernia this Boy was beset,
line_2: And caught (as the Natives are there) in a Net:
I, on a time, from Columbel did get.
As simple birds are caught in fowler's net,
Ev'n so Avara her eyen here did set,

line_1: Now range the Hills, the thickest Woods beset,
line_2: Wind the shrill Horn, or spread the waving Net.

line_1: Secure they trust th' unfaithful Field, beset,
line_2: Till hov'ring o'er 'em sweeps the swelling Net.

line_1: Or the fearful young covey beset;
line_2: Are becoming a prey to the net.

line_1: Shewn fairer now for being beset
Deep in the vale with tufted trees beset;
line_2: Whose leafy arms the summer's rage defeat,

line_1: Deep in the vale with tufted trees beset;
line_2: There stands a country parson's calm retreat.

line_1: Eyes with grim joy the twinkling shoals beset,
line_2: And clasps the quick inextricable net.
Our MARS and VENUS in a net,
Expos'd to sorrow, want, and debt,
